<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 859.001F87/7.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In view of the absence of Mr. Egan and impossibility of sending a Special
                            Representative, owing to lack of time, you will consider this your
                            credentials as Special Envoy for the funeral ceremonies. Explain
                            situation to Foreign Office.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>